<h2>Ideas for mathematical art</h2>



<ul>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics_and_art"
       target="_blank">Wikipedia's article on Mathematics and Art</a>
</li>
<li><a href="http://www.math.tamu.edu/~mboggess/FRACTALS/fractal.html"
       target="_blank">Fractal Art</a>
</li>
<li>The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_number"
       target="_blank">Fibonacci numbers</a>, which often appear 
<a href="http://britton.disted.camosun.bc.ca/fibslide/jbfibslide.htm"
       target="_blank">in nature</a>.
</li>
<li> The Fibonacci numbers are related to the
  <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_ratio"
  target="_blank">golden ratio</a>, which frequently appears in
  <a href="http://britton.disted.camosun.bc.ca/goldslide/jbgoldslide.htm"
  target="_blank">art and architecture</a>.  Here's
  <a href="http://www.goldennumber.net/art.htm" target="_blank">even more
  information.</a>
</li>
<li> Jill Zarestky from TAMU's math department teaches a class on
<a href="http://www.math.tamu.edu/~zarestky/ugst-181.html"
   target="_blank">Arts &amp; Crafts &amp; Maths</a>.  Check out the
final project photos from <a href="http://www.math.tamu.edu/~zarestky/FYS_10.html"
   target="_blank">2010</a> and from
<a href="http://www.math.tamu.edu/~zarestky/FYS_09.html"
   target="_blank">2009</a>.
</li>
<li><a href="http://virtualmathmuseum.org/mathart/index.html"
       target="_blank">Virtual Math Museum exhibit on Math and Art</a>
</li>
<li>Mathematical poetry: <a href="http://mathematicalpoetry.blogspot.com/"
       target="_blank">blog on Mathematical Poetry</a>,
       examples of <a href="http://katherinestange.com/mathweb/"
       target="_blank">mathematical poems</a>, and there are
       many more if you want to <a href="http://www.google.com">search
       for them</a>.
</li>
<li><a href="http://www.origami-fun.com/" target="_blank">Origami!</a>
</li>
<li><a href="http://www.zentangle.com/" target="_blank">Zen Tangles</a>
  and more <a href="http://tanglepatterns.com/" target="_blank">tangle
  patterns</a>.
</li>
<li> You definitely shouldn't miss <a href="http://vihart.com/doodling/"
				      target="_blank">Vi Hart's Doodling
				      in Math Class videos.</a>
</li>
</ul>



